## Fix: Data Sources "Rights" column always Unknown + rename from "Select"

**Context:** The per-table SELECT permission column in the Data Sources grid was
labelled "Select" (confusing next to the row checkboxes) and showed a grey dash
("Unknown") for every table loaded before the probe feature existed. The cell
tooltip told users to "refresh with Update from UC", but the Update-from-UC path
(`merge_table_metadata`) only refreshed columns and comments — it never
re-probed `can_select`, so the column stayed Unknown forever.

**Changes:**
1. `src/front/templates/partials/domain/_domain_metadata.html` — Renamed the
   grid header "Select" → "Rights" (`dm-th-select-perm` th).
2. `src/back/objects/domain/Domain.py` — `merge_table_metadata()` now accepts an
   optional `select_probe` arg and writes `can_select` / `select_error` onto the
   table dict when provided; `update_metadata_tables()` runs
   `check_table_select_permission()` per table and passes the result through, so
   the sync refresh recomputes rights.
3. `src/back/objects/domain/_metadata_tasks.py` — `run_metadata_update_task()`
   (async Update from UC) likewise probes SELECT per table and forwards it to
   `merge_table_metadata()`, so refreshing pre-existing metadata resolves the
   Unknown state.

**Modified files:**
- `src/front/templates/partials/domain/_domain_metadata.html`
- `src/back/objects/domain/Domain.py`
- `src/back/objects/domain/_metadata_tasks.py`

**Test result:** `uv run --frozen pytest -q -k "metadata or unity_catalog or
permission or select or domain"` → 670 passed, 2 skipped, 11 failed. All 11
failures are the pre-existing async event-loop RuntimeErrors in unrelated
endpoints (current-user, review, set-version-status, comments, MCP smoke);
none touch the metadata code changed here.

