## Test: Full domain-lifecycle E2E journey (Playwright)

**Context:** The existing E2E suites are per-endpoint contract tests — each
test does one navigation plus one request. Nothing exercised the *whole*
authoring flow as a single continuous session, where state must accumulate
from step to step (the way it does for a real user). Added a new
`tests/e2e/scenarios/` sub-suite with one journey test that walks the entire
deterministic, session-only lifecycle and asserts the accumulated state at
every hop. The flow alternates genuine DOM interactions (file-input OWL
upload, the "Regenerate" R2RML button) with `page.context.request` mutations
(the same endpoints the page JS hits), proving both the JS wiring and the
session-cookie state-carry. The Databricks-backed tail (UC save/load, KG
build, auto-assign, LLM wizard) is intentionally out of scope and left to the
live-gated suites.

**Changes:**
1. `tests/e2e/scenarios/__init__.py` — New package marker for the journey sub-suite.
2. `tests/e2e/scenarios/test_full_lifecycle.py` — New `TestFullDomainLifecycle::test_create_domain_to_r2rml_journey`. In one browser context (one `DomainSession`): creates a domain (`#domainName` fill + `POST /domain/info`), imports an ontology through the real `#importOwlFileInput` file input (drives the JS → `/ontology/parse-owl`), asserts the imported classes render in `#classHierarchyTree`, saves entity/relationship mappings (`POST /mapping/save`), generates R2RML via the real `#regenerateR2RMLBtn` button, round-trips OWL (`GET /ontology/export-owl`), and snapshots the full domain (`GET /domain/export`). Reuses the existing `sample_owl_content` and `sample_mapping_config` conftest fixtures (their URIs align so the mapping references the imported classes).

**Modified files:**
- `tests/e2e/scenarios/__init__.py` (new)
- `tests/e2e/scenarios/test_full_lifecycle.py` (new)

**Test result:** `ONTOBRICKS_E2E_FAKE_CREDS=1 uv run pytest tests/e2e/scenarios/ --no-cov` → 1 passed; verified stable across 3 consecutive runs (~9.5s each). Deterministic under fake creds (no workspace, warehouse, or LLM required).

