## Test: Live `test_scenario_1` E2E — data-source import → Generate-page OWL → persist

**Context:** The deterministic full-lifecycle journey deliberately skips the
Databricks-backed tail (UC metadata read, the LLM Generate wizard, durable
registry save). This new live-gated scenario covers exactly that tail end-to-end
and, by design, leaves a **durable** domain behind for manual inspection. It
runs against an *already-running* OntoBricks instance (default the local dev
server on `http://localhost:8000`) so the persisted `test_scenario_1` lands in
the same registry the local app reads. The journey: reset → create
`test_scenario_1` with the `databricks-claude-sonnet-4-5` serving endpoint
attached → import the `benoit_cayla.customer` data sources *beforehand*
(`POST /domain/metadata/initialize`) → open the real **Generate** page
(`/ontology?section=wizard`), confirm the imported tables render, and click the
real `#wizardTopGenerateBtn` → the async LLM wizard runs and auto-applies the
generated OWL → poll `/ontology/load` until classes land → `POST
/domain/save-to-uc` and verify the domain is listed. The domain is intentionally
NOT reset at the end.

**Changes:**
1. `tests/e2e/scenarios/test_scenario_1_generate_live.py` — New
   `TestScenario1GenerateLive::test_import_sources_generate_owl_and_persist`.
   Gated behind `ONTOBRICKS_SCENARIO_LIVE=1` (needs a running app + warehouse +
   LLM and mutates the registry). Self-contained fixtures: `scenario_base`
   (health-probes `/health` then `/healthz`, skips cleanly if no app is up) and
   `scenario_page` (a fresh browser context on the running app, bypassing the
   int-workspace `page` fixture so no int bearer is carried). Target/inputs are
   env-overridable (`ONTOBRICKS_LIVE_BASE`, `…_CATALOG`, `…_SCHEMA`, `…_LLM`,
   `…_GEN_TIMEOUT`). Direct POSTs carry the double-submit CSRF token from the
   cookie; generation completion is detected by polling the session truth
   (`/ontology/load`) rather than front-end state.

**Modified files:**
- `tests/e2e/scenarios/test_scenario_1_generate_live.py` (new)

**Test result:** `ONTOBRICKS_SCENARIO_LIVE=1 ONTOBRICKS_LIVE_BASE=http://localhost:8000
uv run pytest tests/e2e/scenarios/test_scenario_1_generate_live.py -v -s --no-cov`
→ 1 passed in 114s against the live local app. The wizard generated an 11-class
ontology (Call, Claim, Contract, Customer, CustomerInteraction, Interaction,
Invoice, Meter, MeterReading, Payment, Subscription) from the 10 imported
`benoit_cayla.customer` tables; `save-to-uc` returned "Domain saved" and
`test_scenario_1` is listed in the registry (persisted for manual inspection).

