## Test: Extend live `test_scenario_1` — Auto-Map (AI mapping) + Knowledge-Graph build

**Context:** Extended the live `test_scenario_1` journey so it now exercises the
*entire* Databricks-backed authoring pipeline end-to-end, not just OWL
generation: after generating the ontology it runs **Auto-Map** (the AI mapping
wizard that generates the SQL + column mappings for every entity/relationship)
and then **builds the knowledge graph** (CREATE VIEW + populate the graph store),
before persisting the durable domain for manual inspection. Several real
behaviours of the persistence/async layer had to be accommodated to make the
journey idempotent and reliably re-runnable.

**Changes:**
1. `tests/e2e/scenarios/test_scenario_1_generate_live.py` — Added two steps to
   the journey and reworked the persistence flow:
   - **Auto-Map**: navigates the real Mapping page (`/mapping?section=autoassign`),
     waits for `MappingState.loadedOntology` to hydrate, then invokes
     `AutoAssignModule.start()` directly (the button re-renders its label/gauges
     on every status tick, so a DOM click races with "element not stable").
     Polls `/mapping/load` until entities carry generated `sql_query` and the
     module is no longer running.
   - **KG build**: `POST /dtwin/sync/start`, then polls `GET /tasks/<id>` (new
     `_poll_task` helper) to terminal state and asserts `completed`.
   - **Idempotent persistence**: at start, deletes any prior `test_scenario_1`
     (`DELETE /settings/registry/domains/{name}`, cache-invalidating) for a clean
     rebuild; immediately claims the registry folder with an initial
     `save-to-uc` (so the async Auto-Map/Build tasks — which persist their domain
     *snapshot* on a background thread — overwrite the folder instead of
     creating a conflicting entry); saves again pre-build and post-build to
     capture the ontology+mappings and the build metadata.
   - New env knobs: `ONTOBRICKS_SCENARIO_AUTOMAP_TIMEOUT` (default 600s),
     `ONTOBRICKS_SCENARIO_BUILD_TIMEOUT` (default 420s). Renamed the test method
     to `test_import_generate_automap_build_and_persist`.

**Modified files:**
- `tests/e2e/scenarios/test_scenario_1_generate_live.py`

**Test result:** `ONTOBRICKS_SCENARIO_LIVE=1 ONTOBRICKS_LIVE_BASE=http://localhost:8000
uv run pytest tests/e2e/scenarios/test_scenario_1_generate_live.py -v -s --no-cov`
→ 1 passed in 396s against the live local app. End-to-end: generated a 10-class
ontology from `benoit_cayla.customer`, Auto-Map produced 10 entity + 9
relationship mappings with SQL, the KG build wrote 35,038 triples in 63s, and
`test_scenario_1` was persisted to the registry for manual inspection. Still
collects + skips cleanly in the default matrix (gated on
`ONTOBRICKS_SCENARIO_LIVE=1`).
